wikipedia_page.main: Henry Wodehouse (born 19 March 1799, Kimberley, Norfolk; died 29 April 1834, Montagu Square, London) was an English cricketer with amateur status. He was associated with Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC) and made his first-class debut in 1828. He played for the Gentlemen in the Gentlemen v Players match.
